  "text_response": "spCadenceRule_INIT (Stored Procedure in TRANSFORMATION_FINANCEHUB schema) is the initialization procedure for the Cadence financial calculations pipeline. Its purpose is to populate the CadenceWorker base table with financial records derived from the staging layer (CadenceExtract_TEST). The procedure: (1) Extracts the latest project names and filters for closed accounting periods, (2) Combines project budget, earned value (EV), and actual cost/hours data at the task and function-location levels from the staging extract, (3) Applies configuration parameters (EV allocation percentage, planned hours threshold) sourced from CONSUMPTION_FINANCEHUB.vDataFilters, (4) Performs initial calculations including function-level actual hours/cost allocation, and (5) Inserts records into CadenceWorker with metadata tracking via audit logs. The initialization step marks records as PENDING, which triggers a cascading pipeline of 15+ downstream allocation and calculation rules (spCadenceRule_Alloc1a/b/c/d, spCadenceRule_EV_Case1-5, spCadenceRule_DEPT, spCadenceRule_RATE, spCadenceRule_RECON, spCadenceRule_SpecExc1/2, etc.) that apply domain-specific business logic to allocate costs across organizational dimensions, compute earned value using multi-stage distribution methods, and perform period-end reconciliation adjustments before finalizing records as COMPLETED.",
